WEBVTT

00:00.400 --> 00:03.351
Okay, Emma is officially...

00:03.352 --> 00:05.678
Renaissance faire ready.

00:05.679 --> 00:07.841
Now, remember, do not kiss

00:07.842 --> 00:09.719
the first prince you meet.

00:09.720 --> 00:11.833
You know, unless it's that new royal baby.

00:13.571 --> 00:15.889
Which in that case, lock that down.

00:16.800 --> 00:19.182
Ooh, preparest thee, fair Emma,

00:19.183 --> 00:21.660
for the grandest time of thee wee life.

00:22.791 --> 00:24.762
I'm not even sure Emma
should be going to this thing.

00:24.763 --> 00:26.392
Ren faire's just full of rowdy dudes

00:26.393 --> 00:28.437
on a quest to take home a drunken wench.

00:28.438 --> 00:29.505
Um, hello.

00:30.085 --> 00:31.919
In that case, lower the drawbridge.

00:31.920 --> 00:33.131
I'm going in.

00:36.887 --> 00:38.543
So, what do you think?

00:38.911 --> 00:40.606
Ren faire can't suck

00:40.607 --> 00:42.491
when you've got friar Tuck.

00:42.492 --> 00:43.887
Yeah.

00:44.197 --> 00:45.576
Emma doesn't have a choice,

00:45.577 --> 00:47.846
but why are you going to the dork ages?

00:48.394 --> 00:49.935
Dude, this is my job.

00:49.936 --> 00:52.063
I'm working on a piece
for "the Mary Hart show."

00:52.064 --> 00:55.697
"Ren faire: Nerds gone wild." (Chuckles)

00:55.698 --> 00:57.880
I'm a respected TV journalist.

00:57.881 --> 00:59.089
Aah.

01:01.315 --> 01:04.822
And Tucker Dobbs reporting
live from the floor.

01:05.609 --> 01:07.377
(Cellphone rings)

01:07.378 --> 01:08.566
It's him. It's your dad.

01:08.567 --> 01:09.602
Answer it. You know the drill.

01:09.603 --> 01:10.692
Right.

01:10.693 --> 01:12.077
The law office of Tucker Dobbs,

01:12.078 --> 01:13.441
how may I direct your call?

01:14.269 --> 01:15.794
Hello, Mr. Dobbs.

01:15.795 --> 01:17.750
Mr. Dobbs is just walking in. Here.

01:18.531 --> 01:20.259
Hey, dad. (Chuckles)

01:21.121 --> 01:22.188
No no no no.

01:22.189 --> 01:23.357
Just getting ready for court.

01:24.536 --> 01:26.139
What's up?

01:26.140 --> 01:28.709
The law office of Tucker Dobbs?

01:28.710 --> 01:30.854
Yeah, Tucker's dad thinks he's a lawyer.

01:30.855 --> 01:32.679
- Since when?
- Since he told him

01:32.680 --> 01:34.114
he graduated from law school.

01:35.099 --> 01:38.510
Okay, but Tucker dropped out of
law school like three years ago.

01:38.511 --> 01:39.843
I know that and you know that,

01:39.844 --> 01:41.561
but his dad doesn't know that.

01:41.562 --> 01:43.072
Why couldn't he just tell him the truth?

01:43.073 --> 01:44.506
Well, in his family, you're a doctor,

01:44.507 --> 01:45.946
you're a lawyer or you're an orphan.

01:47.129 --> 01:48.928
But all Tucker's ever
wanted to do is work in TV.

01:48.929 --> 01:50.293
So I might have suggested

01:50.294 --> 01:52.259
that he drop out and pursue his dream.

01:52.260 --> 01:53.555
Well, has anyone ever suggested

01:53.556 --> 01:55.325
that you stop suggesting things?

01:56.908 --> 01:57.993
All the time.

01:59.473 --> 02:01.380
But his parents never come into the city.

02:01.381 --> 02:03.235
Trust me, it is so not a big deal.

02:05.194 --> 02:06.546
My dad's in town.

02:09.023 --> 02:10.383
And now it's a big deal.

02:11.045 --> 02:12.465
<i>(Theme music plays)</i>

02:13.147 --> 02:16.157
<i>♪ It's amazing how the unexpected ♪</i>

02:16.158 --> 02:19.156
<i>♪ can take your life
and change direction. ♪</i>

02:19.157 --> 02:23.087
Synced and corrected by Nantinha
~ www.addic7ed.com ~

02:23.088 --> 02:25.102
<i>Tucker: You know my dad will freak out,</i>

02:25.103 --> 02:26.598
but I can't keep this up.

02:26.599 --> 02:28.059
You know my knowledge of the law

02:28.060 --> 02:29.538
is limited to TV shows

02:29.539 --> 02:31.176
and that time we went to jury duty

02:31.177 --> 02:32.515
just to pick up girls.

02:33.283 --> 02:34.839
Look, I don't care who she killed.

02:34.840 --> 02:37.478
That defendant was guilty
of first degree sexiness.

02:40.043 --> 02:41.926
You may not know anything about the law,

02:41.927 --> 02:44.011
but we do know someone who does.

02:44.012 --> 02:47.115
Well, unfortunately the
deposed is indisposed

02:47.116 --> 02:50.497
and won't be re-disposed
until an undisclosed time.

02:50.498 --> 02:52.732
So in other words, I'm gonna be a while.

02:52.733 --> 02:53.859
- Oh!
- It's all right. I've got you.

02:54.289 --> 02:57.446
Yes. Yes, you do.

02:58.127 --> 02:59.503
No bones broken, I hope.

02:59.504 --> 03:00.417
Oh, no.

03:01.176 --> 03:02.332
- Riley, are you okay?
- I'm fine.

03:02.894 --> 03:04.070
I'm fine.

03:04.071 --> 03:06.040
Sorry, I'm so clumsy.

03:06.041 --> 03:08.383
Well, you look perfect
from where I'm standing.

03:08.724 --> 03:10.522
Yeah, whatever, man.

03:10.860 --> 03:12.324
Come on, we need your help.

03:14.476 --> 03:15.594
Who is that?

03:15.595 --> 03:16.650
Have you ever seen him before?

03:16.651 --> 03:17.911
What do you know about him?

03:17.912 --> 03:19.209
Riley, if I ever start

03:19.210 --> 03:20.755
noticing the guys who come in here,

03:20.756 --> 03:22.891
it's gonna become a very
different kind of bar.

03:24.868 --> 03:26.332
Okay, I'm gonna need you to tell me

03:26.333 --> 03:28.553
like a dozen lawyery things.

03:28.554 --> 03:30.306
- Ooh, can I borrow these?
- No no no no.

03:30.307 --> 03:31.610
Lawyer-client confidentiality.

03:31.611 --> 03:33.623
Ooh, that's a good one. Keep 'em coming.

03:34.684 --> 03:35.902
You're on your own.

03:35.903 --> 03:37.861
All right, I'm meeting Danny
to finalize our costumes.

03:37.862 --> 03:40.021
I'm kind of playing hooky
for the rest of the afternoon.

03:40.022 --> 03:41.840
Wait, so you're taking the afternoon off

03:41.841 --> 03:43.476
and you won't be back in your office?

03:43.477 --> 03:44.965
Well, not unless I run into my boss

03:44.966 --> 03:46.625
at the wench section at wig world.

03:47.627 --> 03:50.406
So you're not gonna be back
to the office today at all?

03:50.824 --> 03:52.043
<i>Riley: Okay, here's an idea.</i>

03:52.044 --> 03:54.213
All the energy that you use
to act like you're listening,

03:54.214 --> 03:55.956
try using it to actually listen.

03:57.807 --> 03:59.451
Hey, ren boy.

03:59.452 --> 04:00.770
You ready to get medieval?

04:01.454 --> 04:03.360
You have to help me. Mom
wants to come with us.

04:03.361 --> 04:04.929
So the more the merrier, right?

04:04.930 --> 04:06.295
No son ever needs to see

04:06.296 --> 04:07.956
his mother dressed up like a wench.

04:09.219 --> 04:10.769
Don't get me wrong. I'm all for boobs,

04:10.770 --> 04:12.688
just as long as they didn't
feed me at some point.

04:13.752 --> 04:15.097
(Cellphone vibrates)

04:15.098 --> 04:16.473
Oh, no, it's my coach.

04:16.474 --> 04:18.130
I told him I was at home sick in bed.

04:18.132 --> 04:20.694
(Coughs) Hey, coach.

04:20.695 --> 04:22.267
- Oh, hey, mom.
- Oh, hey, honey.

04:23.108 --> 04:24.603
Hey, Riley, I'm glad you're here.

04:24.604 --> 04:26.894
Okay, could you help me with my costume?

04:26.895 --> 04:29.301
You know, I need something
that features the girls,

04:29.302 --> 04:30.896
but is still street legal.

04:32.915 --> 04:36.112
Hey, breadstick, what's
up with the mooney face?

04:36.864 --> 04:39.015
I don't know. Have you ever just like

04:39.016 --> 04:40.181
looked into a guy's eyes

04:40.182 --> 04:41.594
and thought he could be the one?

04:41.595 --> 04:43.220
Yeah, this morning at the bank.

04:43.221 --> 04:44.478
Yesterday at the supermarket.

04:44.930 --> 04:46.788
And two weeks ago at the DMV.

04:47.803 --> 04:49.132
I'm not real choosy.

04:51.294 --> 04:52.827
<i>Wait.</i>

04:52.828 --> 04:54.636
Just now this happened?

04:55.397 --> 04:57.278
I know, I know. It's so silly.

04:57.279 --> 04:59.486
But something about the way he looked at me

04:59.487 --> 05:01.228
literally took my breath away.

05:01.229 --> 05:02.073
Really?

05:02.688 --> 05:05.288
Oh oh, my God. Okay, um...

05:05.289 --> 05:07.420
Well, you... you... you
need to say something.

05:07.799 --> 05:10.054
Oh my God, no. I could never.

05:10.055 --> 05:11.418
I mean, what if he doesn't like me back?

05:11.419 --> 05:12.756
Oh, he does.

05:14.199 --> 05:17.018
Yeah, I mean, you know, what's not to like?

