<i>- (Knocking)
- Ben: Mr. Dobbs.</i>

05:42.399 --> 05:43.789
Come in.

05:44.384 --> 05:46.610
Mr. Dobbs, your dad.

05:46.611 --> 05:47.578
Tucker.

05:47.579 --> 05:48.532
(Laughs)

05:48.987 --> 05:50.454
- Aww.
- (Laughs)

05:50.455 --> 05:51.711
- Uh?
- Uh?

05:52.066 --> 05:53.198
(Awkward laughter)

05:53.199 --> 05:54.364
Well, look at you.

05:54.365 --> 05:55.808
My son the lawyer.

05:55.809 --> 05:58.069
I cannot believe I'm finally
standing in your office.

05:58.779 --> 06:00.101
It's unbelievable.

06:00.420 --> 06:02.285
It most certainly is. (Chuckles)

06:02.984 --> 06:04.257
Now now, Mr. Dobbs,

06:04.258 --> 06:06.147
I think this wall of diplomas begs to...

06:08.481 --> 06:09.957
oh, right, I'm having them cleaned.

06:10.865 --> 06:12.215
Well, dad, now that you've seen

06:12.216 --> 06:14.139
my little corner of the
world, let's go have a drink,

06:14.140 --> 06:15.697
and you can tell me all about yours.

06:15.698 --> 06:17.530
Are you kidding me? I'm not leaving now.

06:19.755 --> 06:21.075
He's not leaving.

06:22.274 --> 06:24.922
Oh, no, I want to hear
about some of your cases.

06:24.923 --> 06:27.338
So what are you working on?

06:27.339 --> 06:28.481
Cases?

06:29.704 --> 06:31.584
Well, uh, there's, uh...

06:31.585 --> 06:33.643
Lawyer-client confidentiality.

06:33.644 --> 06:35.508
Yeah yeah yeah yeah
yeah yeah. What he said.

06:36.438 --> 06:38.262
(Laughs) That's my boy.

06:38.263 --> 06:39.990
Honest as the day is long.

06:39.991 --> 06:42.138
I wouldn't be surprised if
you ended up a judge one day.

06:42.139 --> 06:44.001
Yeah, well, a lot of people would be.

06:46.262 --> 06:47.411
But now that I know

06:47.412 --> 06:49.168
that you're truly passionate about the law,

06:49.820 --> 06:51.581
I'm gonna set you up
with some of my friends.

06:51.582 --> 06:53.395
We're gonna get you a better job.

06:53.396 --> 06:56.128
You know, I'm actually
pretty happy right here.

06:57.385 --> 06:58.568
Are you kidding me?

06:59.003 --> 07:00.141
The guy who gets my coffee

07:00.142 --> 07:01.533
has a bigger office than this.

07:01.534 --> 07:03.473
Yeah, I will have that
to you in like two...

07:03.474 --> 07:04.881
- what are you doing here?
- Honey!

07:09.976 --> 07:13.289
Dad, I'd like you to meet my girlfriend...

07:15.583 --> 07:17.149
Winifred.

07:21.791 --> 07:23.966
Marshall Dobbs. So happy to meet you.

07:23.967 --> 07:25.876
(Laughs) We should go.

07:25.877 --> 07:28.555
Don't forget the Jensens
are expecting us at 8:00.

07:28.556 --> 07:30.815
I told them you'd be
bringing your ambrosia.

07:30.816 --> 07:32.493
Bye, darling. Okay, come on.

07:32.494 --> 07:33.720
(Nervous laughter)

07:39.921 --> 07:42.428
Here, you're probably gonna want this back.

07:44.170 --> 07:45.368
I broke it.

07:47.785 --> 07:48.983
<i>Bonnie: So what do you say, Emma?</i>

07:48.984 --> 07:51.290
Should we saddle him up
and ride him to ren faire?

07:55.793 --> 07:58.243
We are so winning the
costume contest this year.

07:58.244 --> 08:00.649
And wait till you see the skit
that Riley and I been working on.

08:00.650 --> 08:02.806
It's about the black
plague. It's hilarious!

08:03.946 --> 08:06.152
Yeah, okay, honey, but
have you maybe considered

08:06.153 --> 08:09.053
going in a slightly
more romantic direction?

08:09.054 --> 08:10.063
You know, with the skit

08:10.426 --> 08:12.173
and the costume.

08:13.319 --> 08:16.570
Why? This thing's a
guaranteed wench-magnet.

08:16.571 --> 08:17.760
The only thing that would be better

08:17.761 --> 08:19.320
is if I had a unicorn horn.

08:20.940 --> 08:23.101
Turns out those things
are impossible to find.

08:23.102 --> 08:25.158
Yeah yeah, sure. But, honey,

08:25.767 --> 08:27.922
Riley is going with you.

08:27.923 --> 08:30.594
- So?
- Okay, maybe you better sit down.

08:33.219 --> 08:34.763
Yeah, I guess standing is fine.

08:35.664 --> 08:37.303
Okay, remember when I told you

08:37.304 --> 08:39.363
that maybe you should let Riley go?

08:39.717 --> 08:41.783
Well, maybe...

08:41.784 --> 08:43.951
I put the cart before the horse.

08:45.533 --> 08:47.000
Mom, what are you saying?

08:47.001 --> 08:48.705
Oh, no no. I can't, I can't.

08:48.706 --> 08:50.403
Yes yes yes, you can.

08:50.404 --> 08:51.383
Okay.

08:52.116 --> 08:52.980
All right, Danny,

08:52.981 --> 08:55.132
I think that Riley might be into you.

08:55.133 --> 08:56.833
What?! Why do you think that?

08:56.834 --> 08:58.313
Well, she kind of told me.

08:58.314 --> 08:59.859
And now I'm kind of telling you.

08:59.860 --> 09:02.332
- I don't believe you.
- Well, then test the waters.

09:02.333 --> 09:04.522
You know, just put a
little something out there

09:04.523 --> 09:07.022
and see if she gives you
a little something back.

09:07.471 --> 09:09.284
- (Sighs)
- Yeah.

09:12.811 --> 09:13.964
I don't know.

09:13.965 --> 09:16.009
I've been putting out
there for like 15 years.

09:16.010 --> 09:19.635
Yeah, but, Danny, she called you "the one."

09:20.007 --> 09:21.370
The one what?

09:23.302 --> 09:25.572
Okay, I can lead you to water, Danny,

09:26.413 --> 09:28.358
but I can't make you think.

09:31.984 --> 09:34.201
Hey, there's my legal eagle.

09:34.930 --> 09:37.047
How did it go? Does your dad
still think you're a lawyer?

09:37.048 --> 09:38.347
Yep. (Laughs)

09:38.348 --> 09:39.857
Yep, he does.

09:39.858 --> 09:41.355
Dude, that's great.

09:41.356 --> 09:44.040
Yeah, in fact, we ran into his friend Bob.

09:44.041 --> 09:45.973
Yeah, he's also a lawyer.

09:45.974 --> 09:47.455
Owns a big firm.

09:48.071 --> 09:50.387
And I managed to convince him too.

09:51.105 --> 09:52.808
Tucker, man, you're amazing.

09:52.809 --> 09:54.180
Yeah, I know, I am.

09:54.535 --> 09:56.305
There's just one little problem.

09:56.847 --> 09:58.486
Bob offered me a job.

10:00.093 --> 10:01.667
I start on Monday.

10:04.556 --> 10:06.625
He offered you a job
and you actually accepted?!

10:06.626 --> 10:07.668
What's the matter with you?!

10:07.669 --> 10:08.887
I panicked.

10:09.827 --> 10:11.779
But I do get an office with a window.

10:12.578 --> 10:13.928
Good, you can jump out of it

10:13.929 --> 10:15.571
when they find out you're not a lawyer!

10:15.961 --> 10:17.166
Dude, you've got to help me.

10:17.167 --> 10:18.537
What am I gonna do now?

10:18.538 --> 10:21.315
Okay, Tucker, I'm gonna
suggest something drastic,

10:21.316 --> 10:23.872
something crazy, something
even I would never do.

10:25.150 --> 10:26.622
Tell him the truth.

10:28.596 --> 10:29.952
What else you got?

10:30.435 --> 10:32.588
Tucker, man, it's time you stopped lying.

10:32.589 --> 10:34.734
He's your dad. He'll understand.

10:35.147 --> 10:37.345
Face your fears. Follow your dreams.

10:37.346 --> 10:39.331
Let nothing stand in your way.

10:40.109 --> 10:42.087
That sounds a lot like
the speech you gave me

10:42.088 --> 10:44.480
when you talked me into
dropping out of law school.

10:45.946 --> 10:47.811
I thought that sounded familiar.

10:50.686 --> 10:53.049
<i>Danny: "Lovely maiden fair,</i>

10:53.050 --> 10:54.603
look into my...

10:55.636 --> 10:57.089
Heart?

10:57.488 --> 10:59.512
And tell me that you...

11:00.021 --> 11:01.536
Love me."

11:03.253 --> 11:06.053
Um, are you sure about this new skit?

11:06.054 --> 11:07.753
'Cause I kind of miss all the old jokes

11:07.754 --> 11:09.238
about death and sadness.

11:10.378 --> 11:12.102
But the romantic ones always win.

11:12.103 --> 11:13.903
So I thought that maybe
we could switch it up.

11:13.904 --> 11:15.580
- Just keep reading.
- Uh, fine.

11:15.581 --> 11:18.193
"And to you, kind sir,

11:18.194 --> 11:20.352
there is nothing to tell

11:20.353 --> 11:23.298
for my heart has always been true."

11:23.299 --> 11:26.501
"So upon these lips I place a kiss."

11:30.504 --> 11:31.824
Oh my God.

11:31.825 --> 11:33.214
<i>Danny: Oh my God?</i>

11:33.215 --> 11:34.986
"Oh my God" good? Or "oh my God" bad?

11:35.672 --> 11:38.196
So good. Um, amazing, great.

11:38.197 --> 11:40.080
Actually, can we do this again later?

11:40.081 --> 11:42.043
I got to... um, I'll talk to you tomorrow.

11:43.216 --> 11:46.435
Oh! Did you see that?

11:46.436 --> 11:47.461
Mom, you were right.

11:47.462 --> 11:48.867
She really does have feelings for me.

11:48.868 --> 11:51.309
Okay, did I tell you or did I tell you?

11:51.907 --> 11:53.596
You told me. And tomorrow,

11:53.597 --> 11:54.923
I'm gonna tell her.

11:55.271 --> 11:56.909
It's gonna be like a fairy tale.

11:58.354 --> 12:00.148
Yeah, the one where

12:00.149 --> 12:02.396
she rides off into the sunset...

12:03.591 --> 12:04.702
On you.

12:05.864 --> 12:07.823
Maybe we should rethink that costume.

12:08.475 --> 12:09.582
You know, before you give it back,

12:09.583 --> 12:11.364
can I borrow it just for like one weekend?

12:13.708 --> 12:14.773
<i>Tucker: I don't know if I can do this.</i>

12:14.774 --> 12:15.832
Hey, you'll be fine.

12:15.833 --> 12:17.928
Just look your dad in the eye
and tell him the truth.

12:18.445 --> 12:19.803
I'm here for you, man.

12:19.804 --> 12:21.490
<i>- (Knocking on door)
- Oh my God, it's him!</i>

12:22.959 --> 12:24.293
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

12:32.090 --> 12:33.619
There's my legal eagle.

12:33.620 --> 12:35.487
Ready head out and do some celebrating?

12:35.488 --> 12:37.096
Um, yeah, dad, before we go,

12:37.097 --> 12:38.249
we need to talk.

12:38.250 --> 12:39.902
- What's he doing here?
- He lives here.

12:39.903 --> 12:41.088
You live with your assistant?

12:41.089 --> 12:43.187
Yeah, it's part of what I
wanted to talk to you about.

12:44.205 --> 12:45.836
- You're gay?
- I'm not gay.

12:46.414 --> 12:48.249
- Does your girlfriend know?
- I don't have a girlfriend.

12:48.250 --> 12:49.463
Well, I guess we know why.

12:50.280 --> 12:51.814
<i>(Emma cries)</i>

12:51.815 --> 12:53.522
- And you have a baby?
- No, she's not my baby.

12:53.523 --> 12:55.033
She's actually my baby.

12:55.034 --> 12:57.908
Tucker, the least you could do
is adopt your gay lover's child.

12:57.909 --> 13:00.460
- Oh my...
- I thought we raised you right.

13:00.461 --> 13:02.906
No, dad, just... let me start all over.

13:02.907 --> 13:04.862
Okay, we are not gay.

13:04.863 --> 13:06.372
<i>Ben is my friend.</i>

13:07.155 --> 13:08.693
And most importantly...

13:09.957 --> 13:11.430
I'm not a lawyer.

13:11.431 --> 13:12.788
Oh, yes, you are.

13:14.795 --> 13:17.301
I dropped out of law
school after first semester.

13:17.302 --> 13:19.794
I work in TV. I'm trying
to become a producer.

13:19.795 --> 13:20.792
It's my dream.

13:20.793 --> 13:22.092
No, it's not.

13:23.003 --> 13:24.838
Yes. Yes, it is.

13:24.839 --> 13:27.805
I've told you that every time
you've asked me what I wanted to be.

13:27.806 --> 13:29.489
But you got that great scholarship.

13:29.490 --> 13:31.542
I might have lied about that too.

13:32.215 --> 13:34.393
But thanks for that
graduation trip to Mexico.

13:34.394 --> 13:35.794
<i>Fantastico.</i>

13:37.433 --> 13:39.404
So to obtain this so-called dream,

13:39.780 --> 13:41.542
- you decided to lie to me...
- Oh, no.

13:41.543 --> 13:42.834
And to your mother,

13:42.835 --> 13:45.370
to mock us and everything
we value and stand for?

13:45.371 --> 13:47.298
Dad, I'm so sorry.

13:47.299 --> 13:48.213
Oh, don't be.

13:48.529 --> 13:49.879
It's no longer a concern of mine

13:50.471 --> 13:51.627
because from now on,

13:52.324 --> 13:53.680
I no longer have a son.

13:55.686 --> 13:57.511
Wait, dad, let me explain.

14:00.939 --> 14:02.810
You should probably let Bob know

14:02.811 --> 14:04.244
you won't be in on Monday.

14:08.341 --> 14:09.556
- (Babbles)
- Okay.

14:09.557 --> 14:11.304
Listen, if this is lame,

14:11.649 --> 14:13.109
we need to have a signal.

14:13.110 --> 14:14.804
So flap your wings twice

14:14.805 --> 14:17.206
and we will skip out and get tacos.

14:17.889 --> 14:19.309
Yes yes, I know.

14:19.310 --> 14:20.554
Knock knock.

14:20.555 --> 14:23.892
One not-so-fair maiden
reporting for duty.

14:23.893 --> 14:25.682
Oh my gosh, what a coincidence.

14:25.683 --> 14:28.111
That's exactly what I wore to prom.

14:29.216 --> 14:30.473
Uh, where's Danny?

14:30.474 --> 14:32.410
Oh, he asked us to meet
him at the train station.

14:32.411 --> 14:34.602
He had a last minute costume change.

14:35.032 --> 14:38.118
So how's everything on the love front?

14:38.119 --> 14:39.537
You still all breathless?

14:39.538 --> 14:43.274
Yeah, but that may be the corset talking.

14:43.980 --> 14:46.762
So you haven't changed your mind, have you?

14:46.763 --> 14:49.071
No, I saw him yesterday.

14:49.072 --> 14:51.190
And it's all I've been thinking about.

14:51.191 --> 14:52.725
Oh, that's good.

14:53.301 --> 14:55.634
I just wish I at least
knew his name, you know?

14:55.635 --> 14:57.020
Oh, that's not good.

14:57.515 --> 14:59.788
I'm sorry, um, who are you talking about?

14:59.789 --> 15:01.949
The guy from the bar.

15:01.950 --> 15:03.507
Who are you talking about?

15:03.508 --> 15:05.412
The guy from the bar.

15:05.548 --> 15:08.597
I mean, who else would I be talking about?

15:08.598 --> 15:10.303
You know what, Riley? We've got a couple

15:10.304 --> 15:12.020
two, three things to do before we go.

15:12.021 --> 15:13.980
So why don't you just run on ahead

15:13.981 --> 15:15.470
and I will meet you there, okay?

15:15.471 --> 15:16.740
- All right, sounds good.
- All right.

15:16.741 --> 15:19.241
Well, I will see you in medieval times.

15:19.242 --> 15:21.134
- Fair thee...
- Oh my God.

15:21.135 --> 15:23.324
Fair thee... what the hell did I just do?

15:23.325 --> 15:24.408
Okay.

15:24.409 --> 15:25.488
All right.

15:25.489 --> 15:27.085
Okay, Danny, answer.

15:27.086 --> 15:28.257
Answer answer.

15:29.130 --> 15:30.950
- (Emma cries)
- Oh, don't judge me.

15:33.653 --> 15:35.461
<i>(Cellphone rings)</i>

15:36.588 --> 15:38.330
<i>(Ringing continues)</i>

15:40.461 --> 15:42.065
- Mr. Dobbs.
- I have nothing to say to you.

15:42.066 --> 15:43.560
Oh, no, please please.
Just give me two minutes.

15:43.561 --> 15:44.537
That's all I need.

15:44.987 --> 15:47.410
Look, I have no idea what you think of me.

15:47.411 --> 15:48.707
I think you're selfish and immature,

15:48.708 --> 15:50.702
and of indeterminate sexual orientation.

15:52.558 --> 15:53.677
Now we know.

15:54.653 --> 15:56.466
But there's one thing that
you and I have in common.

15:56.862 --> 15:58.358
We're both fathers.

15:58.359 --> 15:59.573
And dad to dad,

15:59.574 --> 16:01.678
I would never turn my
back on my little girl.

16:01.679 --> 16:03.798
Well, you check back with me
in 20 years when she's crushed

16:03.799 --> 16:05.596
all the hopes and dreams
you've had for her.

16:05.597 --> 16:07.800
That's just it! Those
are your hopes and dreams.

16:07.801 --> 16:08.820
Not Tucker's.

16:09.494 --> 16:11.379
Look, you're never around,
so you wouldn't know.

16:11.380 --> 16:13.124
But for the first time in his life,

16:13.125 --> 16:14.313
he's really happy.

16:14.717 --> 16:16.517
He loves working in TV.

16:16.518 --> 16:18.746
You mean poisoning the
minds of millions with crap

16:18.747 --> 16:20.060
repackaged as art?

16:20.061 --> 16:22.168
People seem to like it? I don't...

16:22.898 --> 16:24.949
Just come with me to see him work.

16:24.950 --> 16:26.978
And you'll see how competent
and capable he really is.

16:26.979 --> 16:28.669
And how passionate he is about his work.

16:30.116 --> 16:31.623
I'm thinking you're gonna be very impressed

16:31.624 --> 16:32.929
by what you see.

16:36.005 --> 16:37.252
(Bells ring)

16:39.281 --> 16:41.048
I thought the bells would cheer me up.

16:41.908 --> 16:43.155
They don't...

16:43.689 --> 16:45.440
(Ringing)

16:45.441 --> 16:46.829
Very much.

16:47.834 --> 16:49.093
Danny?

16:49.094 --> 16:51.821
Or should I say, sir Danny?

16:52.319 --> 16:54.185
At your service, milady.

16:55.033 --> 16:56.560
You look amazing.

16:56.907 --> 16:58.046
And you look...

16:59.129 --> 17:00.492
you look amazing.

17:01.667 --> 17:03.456
Like my knight in shining armor.

17:03.936 --> 17:05.289
That was kind of the point.

17:05.667 --> 17:07.624
Riley, I was gonna wait until the ren faire

17:07.625 --> 17:09.105
to tell you this, but that
would just be more time

17:09.106 --> 17:11.286
- without knowing exactly how...
- (Bonnie grunts)

17:12.316 --> 17:13.742
(Pants)

17:13.743 --> 17:15.005
Oh, whew!

17:15.365 --> 17:18.079
Okay, somebody should
check Emma's teeth for bugs

17:18.079 --> 17:21.272
because we just set some
sort of stroller speed record.

17:21.273 --> 17:22.893
Uh, mom, we're in the middle of something.

17:22.894 --> 17:24.194
Yeah, and if you get to the end of it,

17:24.195 --> 17:25.823
it's going to be the end of me.

17:25.824 --> 17:28.710
Danny, me thinks thou
should shutteth uppeth.

17:29.344 --> 17:31.643
Not now. Riley, you need to hear this.

17:31.644 --> 17:33.862
Ow ow, easy there, robo-knight.

17:33.863 --> 17:36.019
Excuse me, is this knight bothering you?

17:36.020 --> 17:37.771
- She's fine.
- I wasn't talking to you.

17:37.772 --> 17:38.956
- I'm fine.
- You heard her.

17:38.957 --> 17:40.527
Again, not talking to you.

17:40.528 --> 17:41.911
Fine because I think we're done talking.

17:41.912 --> 17:43.476
Is that how we're playing it?

17:43.477 --> 17:44.811
It most certainly is.

17:46.625 --> 17:47.643
No no no.

17:48.294 --> 17:49.365
Oh, Danny!

17:50.102 --> 17:51.584
- Bonnie: Danny, no, Danny.
- Riley: Stop. Stop it.

17:51.585 --> 17:52.827
Stop, okay. (Screams)

17:52.828 --> 17:54.067
<i>Bonnie: Okay, all right. Here we go.</i>

17:54.068 --> 17:55.335
Here we go, all right.

17:55.336 --> 17:56.263
Danny, stop.

17:56.640 --> 17:58.248
<i>- (Riley screams)
- Bonnie: Danny!</i>

17:58.249 --> 17:59.394
- Oh my God.
- Oh no.

18:00.162 --> 18:01.733
<i>Danny, no no no.</i>

18:02.489 --> 18:03.470
<i>Bonnie:  Stop it.</i>

18:03.471 --> 18:04.774
I got your back, Danny!

18:04.775 --> 18:06.231
Eat bells, tin man!

18:08.887 --> 18:10.514
- (Grunting)
- (Screaming)

18:15.084 --> 18:16.215
Dad?

18:17.771 --> 18:19.664
Well, I know I'm impressed.

18:19.665 --> 18:21.133
How about you?

18:21.734 --> 18:23.249
Oh my God, Danny. Are you okay?

18:24.032 --> 18:25.544
You are such a jerk.

18:28.604 --> 18:30.451
Oh my God, are you okay?

18:30.774 --> 18:32.295
You are such a jerk.

18:33.796 --> 18:35.096
I was afraid I'd never see you again.

18:35.963 --> 18:37.172
I'm Philip.

18:37.173 --> 18:38.599
I'm Riley.

18:38.600 --> 18:40.853
What are the chances we'd
both be going to ren faire?

18:41.599 --> 18:43.058
Unless you're an actual knight.

18:43.419 --> 18:44.811
That's cool too.

18:46.190 --> 18:47.707
This is him.

18:48.011 --> 18:51.722
Oh, so that's the one.

18:51.723 --> 18:55.775
Yeah, it turns out he's the one.

18:55.776 --> 18:57.638
Yeah, I got that part.

18:58.246 --> 19:00.369
Um, look, Danny, I am so...

19:00.991 --> 19:03.899
why do people even listen to me?

19:03.900 --> 19:06.094
(Laughs) Damsel in distress!

19:06.095 --> 19:07.519
Coming through!

19:10.509 --> 19:12.004
Dad, what are you doing here?

19:12.005 --> 19:14.113
I just brought him by to see you at work.

19:14.856 --> 19:16.383
And I've seen enough.

19:16.384 --> 19:17.443
Oh, hell no.

19:17.444 --> 19:19.891
You don't get to walk away from me twice.

19:20.722 --> 19:22.501
Do you know what being a dad means?

19:23.301 --> 19:25.358
Unconditional love and support.

19:25.359 --> 19:26.746
And you know who taught me that?

19:26.747 --> 19:28.191
Ben.

19:28.192 --> 19:29.620
Oh, thanks, man.

19:30.387 --> 19:32.058
You might want to take your
hat off, I'm just saying.

19:34.771 --> 19:36.368
But it should have been you.

19:37.165 --> 19:39.351
So you can pretend you don't have a son,

19:39.352 --> 19:41.016
disown me, whatever. I don't care.

19:41.017 --> 19:42.894
I'm done lying about what I do.

19:42.895 --> 19:45.286
I'm following my dream and I'm happy.

19:47.345 --> 19:48.828
This is who I am.

19:51.582 --> 19:53.270
Now you can go.

19:54.307 --> 19:55.653
That was a great speech.

19:57.775 --> 20:00.129
Reminds me of the one
I wish I'd given my dad.

20:01.914 --> 20:03.301
What are you saying?

20:03.747 --> 20:05.299
What I'm saying is

20:06.666 --> 20:08.179
I made a mistake.

20:09.546 --> 20:10.929
And I'm sorry...

20:11.308 --> 20:13.042
That I've been so closed-minded.

20:14.414 --> 20:16.112
But what I'm really saying is

20:16.883 --> 20:18.554
is that I'm very proud

20:19.392 --> 20:21.907
to call you my son.

20:33.880 --> 20:36.015
That was a great speech, Tucker.

20:36.501 --> 20:38.411
Maybe you should have been a lawyer.

20:38.412 --> 20:39.969
(Mouths)

20:43.288 --> 20:44.291
<i>Bonnie: Are you okay?</i>

20:44.637 --> 20:45.808
I'm fine.

20:46.919 --> 20:49.747
Except I lost the instructions
on how to get out of this suit.

20:51.383 --> 20:53.078
I'm really sorry about Riley.

20:53.633 --> 20:54.873
Don't be.

20:54.874 --> 20:56.170
It's all good.

20:56.171 --> 20:58.506
Riley might think she found
her knight in shining armor,

20:58.507 --> 20:59.987
but I know how this story ends.

20:59.988 --> 21:01.226
With me.

21:02.022 --> 21:03.313
I'm her prince charming.

21:05.344 --> 21:08.579
Then, to your happily ever after.

